    "causal_summary": "The GitKraken MCP integration program (see `../spec.md`) needs ground truth before any file changes: the GitHub README under-documents the real tool surface (it names only 3 example tools against a real 31), the correct `.utcpconfig.json` config shape isn't obvious (the CLI's own config generator emits a machine-local form, not the repo's portable `npx` convention), and whether to register the server read-only or read+write is a real safety tradeoff against sk-git's existing ask-first/no-direct-branch/conventional-commit rules",
